---
// Problem + Agitate section. Every stat below is a published industry figure (not an
// internal customer outcome). Sources listed beneath each card so a reader can verify.
---
<section id="agitate" class="relative bg-navy-900 text-white py-24 md:py-32 overflow-hidden">
  <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.04]" style="background-image:
    linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,1) 1px, transparent 1px),
    linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255,255,255,1) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 64px 64px;
    mask-image: radial-gradient(ellipse at center, black 30%, transparent 85%);
    -webkit-mask-image: radial-gradient(ellipse at center, black 30%, transparent 85%);"></div>

  <div class="relative max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
    <p class="eyebrow text-prizm-400 reveal">The honest part</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 text-h1 font-bold reveal">
      You are not slow.<br/>
      <span class="text-white/50">Your stack is.</span>
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-10 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-16 gap-y-8 text-lg text-white/80 leading-relaxed reveal">
      <p>
        You open a spreadsheet. You open a carrier portal. You open the customs broker&#39;s PDF rate card.
        You open Outlook, then the TMS, then QuickBooks, then the BOL generator, then Slack to ask
        an ops teammate for a PRO number. You do this <em class="not-italic text-white">for every single quote</em>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Meanwhile the shipper who emailed you at 9:14 AM is already at lunch with another forwarder.
        <strong class="text-white">Nine out of ten shippers expect a quote inside two hours</strong>,
        yet industry survey data puts most manual quoting at six or more.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ul class="mt-14 grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6 reveal">
      <li class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 p-6 bg-white/[0.03]">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-prizm-400 tracking-widest uppercase">15–30</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold">disconnected systems</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/60">per mid-market freight forwarder, reportedly draining up to 20–30% of annual revenue through poor data quality.</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[11px] text-white/40 font-mono">Source: Logi-Sys, 2024</p>
      </li>
      <li class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 p-6 bg-white/[0.03]">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-prizm-400 tracking-widest uppercase">$100–$400</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold">per container per day</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/60">in demurrage and detention fees, frequently discovered 30+ days later on the carrier invoice.</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[11px] text-white/40 font-mono">Source: FreightAmigo, 2025</p>
      </li>
      <li class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 p-6 bg-white/[0.03]">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-prizm-400 tracking-widest uppercase">3–7%</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold">of freight spend, leaking</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/60">on carrier invoice errors rarely reconciled manually. For a $10M forwarder, that&#39;s $300K–$700K a year.</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[11px] text-white/40 font-mono">Source: Freightify, 2025</p>
      </li>
      <li class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 p-6 bg-white/[0.03]">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-prizm-400 tracking-widest uppercase">$500K · $1M</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold">per ITAR violation</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/60">civil and criminal exposure, per incident. Forwarders are now compliance gatekeepers by statute, not neutral carriers.</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[11px] text-white/40 font-mono">Source: 22 CFR § 127.10</p>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="mt-14 max-w-2xl text-white/70 text-base reveal">
      <p>
        The tools most mid-market operators have either weren&#39;t built for them — they were built for
        companies ten times their size — or were spun up from a spreadsheet five years ago. Neither is good
        enough anymore.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
